<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-MwhAMqPzeTu5fBRUMf2ntg" name="define_portf_structures_and_metrics,_3YHHA_7SEd2qlKqF0pYYYg" guid="-MwhAMqPzeTu5fBRUMf2ntg" changeDate="2009-10-15T14:32:19.667-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    These&amp;nbsp;structures and measurements&amp;nbsp;represent governance control points that are critical to ensure that the&#xD;
    detailed actions and investments undertaken by the&amp;nbsp;organization are conducted in a manner consistent with the&#xD;
    desired business direction. Several dimensions of the organization's strategies are represented within the targets and&#xD;
    measurements:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Alignment with strategic direction&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Financial viability (cost and revenues)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Technical feasibility&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Acceptable risk thresholds&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Capacity constraints (resource availability and skill mix)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Portfolio balance and mix&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To define the complete set of measurements and targets that&amp;nbsp;ensure the ongoing &#xD;
connection between the organization's strategic planning process and the selection &#xD;
and execution of&amp;nbsp;portfolio components.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
